 BY AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI GOVERNOR David Umahi of Ebonyi State has approved the commencement of promotion exercise for all civil servants in the state. The Governor, in a statement signed by his Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Francis Nwaze, directed that the promotion be based on available vacancies. He said the exercise, which had been on hold since 2015, should commence from 2021. The Governor explained that the promotion was based on vacancy created by retired civil servants or other occurrences. The statement read, “The Governor of Ebonyi State, Engr. Chief David Nweze Umahi, FNSE, FNATE has again, graciously approved the promotion of civil servants in Ebonyi State based on available vacancy and this is to commence from 2021. “The Governor explained that promotion is based on vacancy created by those retired or other occurrences which might have caused a vacancy in the service. “Furthermore, Governor Umahi directs heads of different MDAs to immediately commence a compilation of all vacancies in their MDAs and schedule for a written promotion examination which will be the determinant of those to be promoted.” Recall that there had been a ban on promotion of civil servants and employment into the Ebonyi civil service since 2015.  